  "instructions": [
    "Blend fermented pilchards with salt, black pepper, cumin, and coriander to create a marinade.",
    "Heat olive oil in a salt-block vessel over low heat.",
    "Add onion and garlic to the vessel and cook until softened.",
    "Add lemongrass to the vessel and cook for an additional 2 minutes.",
    "Add the marinade to the vessel, stirring to combine.",
    "Add water to the vessel and bring to a simmer.",
    "Reduce heat to low and cook for 20 minutes.",
    "Season the pilchards tagine with additional salt and black pepper if desired.",
    "Serve the tagine over couscous or with crusty bread."
